                        <pb n="667"/> HORSHAM. <persName>
                           <forename>Godfrey</forename> de <surname>Crokhurst</surname>
                        </persName> grants to <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> ate
                 <surname>Denne</surname>
                        </persName> and <persName nymRef="Crokhurst">
                           <forename>Joan</forename>
                        </persName> his wife one messuage and 14 acres of arable land in a field called '<placeName type="minor">Brodefeld</placeName>' in the parish of <placeName key="place_102078">Horsham</placeName>, also the reversion of 13 acres and 1 rood in
                        <placeName key="place_102047">Crokhurst</placeName> with other lands in Crokhurst and Horsham. Dated at <placeName role="date" key="place_102078">Horsham</placeName> the <origDate when="1321-06-18">Thursday next after the feast of the Holy Trinity,
